////Rotator cuff - Partial lesions

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 - AC-Joint & Rotator Cuff of Shoulder MRI
And I select the radio button 'Finding'
And I select 'Rotator cuff' from the Finding dropdown

When I select 'Partial lesions' radio button
Then 'Supraspinatus (SSP)' radio button is enabled
And 'Subscapularis (SSC)' radio button is enabled
And 'Infraspinatus (ISP)' radio button is enabled
And 'Teres minor (TM)' radio button is enabled
And 'partial-thickness tear' radio button is enabled
And 'Degeneration' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Supraspinatus (SSP)' radio button
Then 'Articular-sided (Snyder A)' radio button is enabled
And 'Bursa-sided (Snyder B)' radio button is enabled
And 'Interstitiell' radio button is enabled
And 'Myotendinous junction' radio button is enabled
And 'Proximal' radio button is enabled
And 'Insertion / Footprint' radio button is enabled
And 'Length' input field is enabled
And 'Depth' input field is enabled
And 'Bayne und Bateman' radio button is enabled
And 'Snyder' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Articular-sided (Snyder A)' radio button
Then 'With sGHL = Pulley type 2' radio button is enabled
And 'With sGHL & partial rupture articular-sided cranial SSC = Pulley type 4' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Insertion / Footprint' radio button
Then 'PASTA lesion' radio button is enabled
And 'Reversed PASTA' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Bayne und Bateman' radio button
Then 'Grade I: < 1 cm' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade II: 1 – 3 cm' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade III: 3 – 5 cm' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade IV: > 5 cm' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Snyder' radio button
Then '0: Intact RTC' radio button is enabled
And 'I: < 1 cm, Synovitis' radio button is enabled
And 'II: 1 cm, Tendons splicing, partial thickness tear' radio button is enabled
And 'III: < 3 cm, fragmentation' radio button is enabled
And 'IV: > 3 cm, severe proximal RM partial tear, flap tear' radio button is enabled
